input: The James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) has captured its first direct image of a planet outside our solar system. The exoplanet, HIP 65426 b, is a gas giant about six to 12 times the mass of Jupiter. It is young, about 15 to 20 million years old, compared to our 4.5-billion-year-old Earth. Astronomers used four different light filters on JWST’s Near-Infrared Camera (NIRCam) and Mid-Infrared Instrument (MIRI) to capture the planet.
